GODILThe AtomGodilVideo project is an FPGA based video adapter for the Acorn Atom. It uses a OHO-Elektronik GODIL40 XC3S250E FPGA module to replace the Atom's existing mc6847 Video Display Generator (VDG).The GODIL contains several registers controlling it's operation, plus the SID registers. All of the registers are read/write, unless otherwise stated.Description 	          AddressUART Data Reg            `BDB0UART Control/Status Reg  `BDB1UART Baud Rate Reg       `BDB2SID Registers            `BDC0Mode Extension Reg       `BDE0Character Address Reg    `BDE1VGA80x40 HW Cursor Col   `BDE2VGA80x40 Hw Cursor Row   `BDE3VGA80x40 Control Reg 1   `BDE4VGA80x40 Control Reg 2   `BDE5Horizontal Scroll Offset `BDE6Vertical Scroll Offset   `BDE7Pointer X Location       `BDE8Pointer Y Location       `BDE9Pointer Control/Status   `BDEAScroll Left Margin       `BDEBScroll Right Margin      `BDECScroll Top Margin        `BDEDScroll Bottom Margin     `BDEEVersion                  `BDEFCharacter Data Registers `BDF0In VGA80x40 mode the characters are stored in video memory from #8000-#8C7F. If enabled, the attributes are stored from #8C80-#98FF.